recording.title: Something in the Way / Endless, Nameless

annotation:
Version containing the "secret" unlisted track "Endless Nameless" several minutes after "Something in the Way" has faded out. Various catalogue numbers and record labels have been associated with this release.
The UK version, for instance, has two catalogue numbers, was manufactured in Germany and distributed by BMG/MCA until Universal took over the rights to the Geffen label in 1998.
Full details of the large number of different pressings of the European "Nevermind" can be found at [http://www.sliver.it/nirvana/test/pages/official/nevermind/germany.html]

== Sub-Optimal Credits ==
Recorded at Sound City, Van Nuys, CA
Mixed at Scream, Studio City, CA
Mastered at Masterdisk, New York City, NY
Management: Danny Goldberg and John Silva for Gold Mountain Entertainment
Legal Affairs: Alan Mintz/Ziffren, Brittenham & Brence
A&R: Gary Gerah

Monkey Photo: Kurt Cobain
Cover Photo: Kirk Waddle (with Spencer Eldin as the model; not listed but common knowledge by now ;)
